FOODBORNE ILLNESS - USA (04): (NEW YORK) REFRIED BEANS, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*******************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 14 Oct 2016
Source: Time Warner Cable News [edited]
http://www.twcnews.com/nys/buffalo/news/2016/10/14/mighty-taco-foodborne-illness-cause-erie-niagara-counties-.html


The cause behind the foodborne illness that made more than 140 Mighty Taco customers sick could be released as early as Friday, 14 Oct 2016. Erie County [New York State] Health Department officials who work at the Rath Building say a sample from those beans was sent away a week ago as part of a state health department investigation. Friday is the earliest the organization could release the results, although they caution results could take weeks to come in.

On Thursday, 13 Oct 2016, Mighty Taco named Pennsylvania company Pellegrino Food Products as the manufacturer of the bad beans. At least 142 people in Erie and Niagara counties who ate those beans between 23 Sep 2016 and 6 Oct 2016 complained of nausea and vomiting. No one has reported getting sick since Mighty Taco removed the beans.

The company also took to Facebook on Thursday night to answer common questions that many customers had and ensured them this was a "isolated and unprecedented situation that we have not encountered in our 43 year history of serving the Western New York public."

"Pellegrino Food Products Co, Inc stands behind the quality of all of its products and takes food safety issues very seriously. Refried beans are manufactured exclusively for Mighty Taco. To Pellegrino Food's knowledge, no root cause has yet been determined of the reported illnesses, and we are actively working with the Pennsylvania Department of Agriculture in its investigation," Pellegrino Foods Production Co said in a statement.

